    <div class="section">
      

<div id="review_904728355" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/904728355" />
    <a title="Emily Crall" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/6938526-emily-crall"><img alt="Emily Crall" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1609109902p2/6938526.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/904728355?book_show_action=true">Apr 08, 2014</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Emily Crall" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Emily Crall" href="/user/show/6938526-emily-crall">Emily Crall</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was ok"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was ok</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Hardcover 9781451645606" href="/book/show/16130477-a-house-in-the-sky">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6938526-emily-crall?shelf=memoir">memoir</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/6938526-emily-crall?shelf=non-fiction">non-fiction</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer904728355" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer11794933744452736911">I really wanted to like this book, but I was deeply disappointed. The book itself was well-written, much of that I assume to be the result of Sara Corbett&apos;s contribution. As I was reading, I lamented to my husband how angry I was at Amanda for bringing this on herself and Nigel. No one deserves the rape and torture she/they endured, but her naive passport-stamping and country-counting desire to see the world was repulsive. My husband even asked, &quot;So when she was traveling, was she doing mission </span>
  <span id="freeText11794933744452736911" style="display:none">I really wanted to like this book, but I was deeply disappointed. The book itself was well-written, much of that I assume to be the result of Sara Corbett's contribution. As I was reading, I lamented to my husband how angry I was at Amanda for bringing this on herself and Nigel. No one deserves the rape and torture she/they endured, but her naive passport-stamping and country-counting desire to see the world was repulsive. My husband even asked, "So when she was traveling, was she doing mission work or anything?" To which I had to respond, "No." She was simply traveling for her own desire. She became indifferent to dangers, thinking that nothing bad would ever happen to her. She ignored common sense and advice from others, instead trying to be this macho woman who could do whatever she wanted. <br /><br />Her entire trip to Somalia was based on this idiotic belief that she could get money (to further support her travels) by writing a few good stories there since it was an easy destination in that no other media would dare go there. The stories were hers from which to garnish wages. As for the "lack of help" from the Australian and Canadian governments, I can't help but side with them a bit. If your country highly recommends you don't enter another country, and you decide to go anyway...well, it's kind of an, "I told you so." <br /><br />All in all, I couldn't get over my frustration and anger at Amanda's selfishness, naivety, and ignorance enough to actually connect with the book. </span>
  <a data-text-id="11794933744452736911" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


      <div class="reviewFooter uitext buttons">
          

